<key pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" box="[151,1435,222,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,222,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<number box="[151,164,222,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="1.0">1</number>
. Carapace with transverse piliferous striations, interrupted at grooves delimiting regions.............................. 
<number box="[1423,1435,222,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="2.0">2</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" box="[151,1435,251,272]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,251,272]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
- Carapace nearly smooth, some striation on posterolateral region................................................ 
<number box="[1423,1435,251,272]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="3.0">3</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<number box="[151,165,281,302]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="2.0">2</number>
. Single strong epibranchial spine on carapace. Gape of cheliped fingers thickly pubescent, palm with convex extensor margin........................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1435,309,331]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galathinus">
<emphasis box="[1311,1435,309,331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">P. galathinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
- Two strong epibranchial spines on carapace. Gape of cheliped fingers not pubescent, palm with nearly straight extensor margin.......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1436,369,390]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosariensis">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,369,390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">P. rosariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" box="[151,1435,398,419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,398,419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<number box="[151,165,398,419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="3.0">3</number>
. Both inner and outer orbital angles not produced; ocular peduncle not pubescent next to the cornea............. 
<taxonomicName box="[1333,1435,398,419]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[1333,1435,398,419]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
- Inner and/or outer orbital angles produced into small and acute spine; ocular peduncle fringed with short simple setae next to cornea............................................................................................. 
<number box="[1423,1435,457,478]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="4.0">4</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<number box="[151,165,486,507]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" value="4.0">4</number>
. Inner orbital angle produced into acute spine. Propodus of cheliped smooth, gape of fingers pubescent on ventral surface................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName box="[1326,1435,515,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenus">
<emphasis box="[1326,1435,515,536]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">P. amoenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="185">
- Inner orbital angle not produced. Propodus of cheliped with longitudinal crest, gape of fingers not pubescent on ventral surface.......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1303,1435,574,595]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[1303,1435,574,595]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="185">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
